'''Lester Allen''' (November 17, 1891 – November 6, 1949) was a screen, stage, vaudeville, circus actor, and film director. In [[vaudeville]], he appeared in a double act with [[Nellie Breen]] and also emceed at the [[Palace Theatre, New York|Palace Theatre]].<ref>Laurie, Joe, Jr. ''Vaudeville: From the Honky-tonks to the Palace.'' New York: Henry Holt, 1953. p. 230, 489.</ref>
==Selected filmography== {{div col|colwidth=23em}} * ''[[Love That Brute]]'' (1950) * ''[[Ma and Pa Kettle Go to Town]]'' (1950) * ''[[Ma and Pa Kettle]]'' (1949) * ''[[That Lady in Ermine]]'' (1948) * ''[[The Heat's On]]'' (1948) * ''[[Crime on Their Hands]]'' (1948) * ''[[The Pirate (1948 film)|The Pirate]]'' (1948) * ''Fun on a Weekend'' (1947) * ''[[The Dark Mirror (film)|The Dark Mirror]]'' (1946) * ''[[The Dolly Sisters (film)|The Dolly Sisters]]'' (1946) * ''[[The Great Flamarion]]'' (1945) * ''[[Klondike Kate (film)|Klondike Kate]]'' (1943) {{div col end}}
==Death== Allen was struck and killed while crossing [[Ventura Boulevard]] in the [[San Fernando Valley]].{{citation needed|date=April 2011}}
